onChange.script:
"""
    Updates row count when rawDataset changes.
    """
    rawDataset = self.view.custom.rawDataset
    if rawDataset is not None:
        self.view.custom.rowCount = rawDataset.getRowCount()
    else:
        self.view.custom.rowCount = 0

selected = self.view.custom.selectedColumn
    raw_data = self.view.custom.rawData
    table = self.getSibling("Table")

    system.perspective.print("=== DROPDOWN CHANGED ===")
    system.perspective.print("Selected: " + str(selected))
    system.perspective.print("Raw data: " + str(raw_data))

    if not selected or not raw_data:
        system.perspective.print("Nothing to update.")
        table.props.data = []
        return

    if selected == "All":
        system.perspective.print("Showing ALL columns.")
        table.props.data = raw_data
    else:
        filtered_data = []
        for row in raw_data:
            value = row.get(selected, None)
            filtered_data.append({selected: value})

        system.perspective.print("Filtered data: " + str(filtered_data))
        table.props.data = filtered_data

config.script:
dataset = self.view.custom.editableDataset
	success = True
	error_message = None
	
	try:
	    for row in range(dataset.rowCount):
	        params = {
	            "Timestamp": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Timestamp"),
	            "Availability": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Availability (%)"),
	            "Performance": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Performance (%)"),
	            "Quality": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Quality (%)"),
	            "OEE": dataset.getValueAt(row, "OEE (%)"),
	            "ProductionCount": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Production Count"),
	            "RejectionCount": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Rejection Count"),
	            "Downtime": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Downtime (min)"),
	            "IdleTime": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Idle Time (min)"),
	            "AvgCycleTime": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Average Cycle Time (s)"),
	            "EffectiveCycleTime": dataset.getValueAt(row, "Effective Cycle Time (s)")
	        }
	
	        # The path must exactly match the Named Query's path in the Ignition Designer
	        system.db.runNamedQuery("ExcelUpload/MyMergeQuery/MergeExcelRow", params)
	
	except Exception as e:
	    success = False
	    error_message = str(e)
	
	if success:
	    system.perspective.openPopup(
	        "successPopup",
	        "Task/Error Popup/Error Popup",
	        {"customMessage": "Upload completed successfully!"},
	        title="Success",
	        modal=True,
	        width=500,
	        height=200
	    )
	else:
	    system.perspective.openPopup(
	        "errorPopup",
	        "Task/Error Popup/Error Popup",
	        {"customMessage": "Upload failed: " + error_message},
	        title="Error",
	        modal=True,
	        width=500,
	        height=200
	    )

# Get the table's dataset
	dataset = self.props.data
	
	# Row that was edited
	rowIndex = event.row
	
	# Determine column name
	if isinstance(event.column, int):
	    # event.column is index
	    columnIndex = event.column
	    columnName = list(dataset.columnNames)[columnIndex]
	else:
	    # event.column is already column name
	    columnName = event.column
	
	# New value from the edit
	newValue = event.value
	
	# Optional: match type with old value
	oldValue = dataset.getValueAt(rowIndex, columnName)
	expectedType = type(oldValue)
	try:
	    if expectedType is not type(None):
	        newValue = expectedType(newValue)
	except:
	    pass
	
	# Update dataset
	dataset = system.dataset.setValue(dataset, rowIndex, columnName, newValue)
	
	# Apply back to table
	self.props.data = dataset
	self.view.custom.editableDataset = dataset

"""
	Handles dropdown column filtering for table display in Perspective.
	Dynamically updates props.columns so only selected columns appear.
	"""
	
	# Get selected columns from dropdown
	selected_columns = self.props.value
	raw_dataset = self.view.custom.editableDataset
	table = self.getSibling("Table")
	
	# If no dataset or selection, clear the table
	if not raw_dataset or not selected_columns:
	    table.props.data = []
	    table.props.columns = []
	    return
	
	import system.dataset
	
	# Convert dataset to Python list of dicts
	col_names = list(raw_dataset.getColumnNames())
	pyds = system.dataset.toPyDataSet(raw_dataset)
	data_list = [{col_names[i]: row[i] for i in range(len(col_names))} for row in pyds]
	
	# Decide which columns to keep
	if "All" in selected_columns:
	    final_columns = col_names
	else:
	    final_columns = selected_columns
	
	# Filter rows to selected columns
	filtered_rows = [
	    [row.get(col) for col in final_columns] for row in data_list
	]
	
	# Build dataset for table data
	new_dataset = system.dataset.toDataSet(final_columns, filtered_rows)
	table.props.data = new_dataset
	
	# Build column configs dynamically
	default_column_template = {
	    "visible": True,
	    "editable": True,
	    "render": "auto",
	    "justify": "auto",
	    "align": "center",
	    "resizable": True,
	    "sortable": True,
	    "sort": "none",
	    "filter": {
	        "enabled": False,
	        "visible": "on-hover",
	        "string": {"condition": "", "value": ""},
	        "number": {"condition": "", "value": ""},
	        "boolean": {"condition": ""},
	        "date": {"condition": "", "value": ""}
	    },
	    "boolean": "checkbox",
	    "number": "value",
	    "progressBar": {
	        "max": 100, "min": 0,
	        "value": {"enabled": True, "format": "0,0.##", "justify": "center"}
	    },
	    "nullFormat": {"includeNullStrings": False, "strict": False, "nullFormatValue": ""},
	    "numberFormat": "0,0.##",
	    "dateFormat": "MM/DD/YYYY",
	}
	
	# Apply default template to each selected column
	dynamic_columns = []
	for col in final_columns:
	    col_config = dict(default_column_template)  # copy template
	    col_config["field"] = col
	    col_config["header"] = {"title": col, "justify": "left", "align": "center"}
	    dynamic_columns.append(col_config)
	
	# Assign dynamic columns
	table.props.columns = dynamic_columns

"""
    Handles Excel file upload, validates headers, populates rawDataset (as real dataset), 
    and formats Timestamp values.
    """
    from java.io import ByteArrayInputStream
    from org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel import WorkbookFactory, CellType
    from java.text import SimpleDateFormat
    from java.util import Calendar

    required_headers = [
        "Timestamp",
        "Availability (%)",
        "Performance (%)",
        "Quality (%)",
        "OEE (%)",
        "Production Count",
        "Rejection Count",
        "Downtime (min)",
        "Idle Time (min)",
        "Average Cycle Time (s)",
        "Effective Cycle Time (s)"
    ]

    fileBytes = event.file.bytes
    inputStream = ByteArrayInputStream(fileBytes)

    # Get UI components
    label = self.getSibling("Label")
    table = self.getSibling("Table")

    def markInvalid(message):
        label.props.text = "Invalid Table"
        label.props.style.color = "red"
        table.props.data = []
        system.perspective.openPopup(
            "errorPopup",
            "Task/Error Popup/Error Popup",
            {"customMessage": message},
            title="Error",
            modal=True,
            width=500,
            height=200
        )

    try:
        workbook = WorkbookFactory.create(inputStream)
    except Exception as e:
        markInvalid("Error reading Excel file. Ensure it's valid.\n" + str(e))
        inputStream.close()
        return

    if workbook.getNumberOfSheets() == 0:
        markInvalid("The uploaded workbook does not contain any sheets.")
        inputStream.close()
        return

    sheet = workbook.getSheetAt(0)
    headerRow = sheet.getRow(0)

    if headerRow is None:
        markInvalid("The first sheet is empty and does not have a header row.")
        inputStream.close()
        return

    # Read actual headers
    actual_headers = []
    for colIndex in range(headerRow.getFirstCellNum(), headerRow.getLastCellNum()):
        cell = headerRow.getCell(colIndex)
        if cell and cell.getCellType() == CellType.STRING:
            actual_headers.append(cell.getStringCellValue().strip())

    required_set = {h.lower() for h in required_headers}
    actual_set = {h.lower() for h in actual_headers}

    missing_headers = required_set - actual_set
    extra_headers = actual_set - required_set

    if missing_headers or extra_headers:
        msg = ""
        if missing_headers:
            msg += "Missing headers: " + ", ".join(missing_headers) + "\n"
        if extra_headers:
            msg += "Extra headers: " + ", ".join(extra_headers)
        markInvalid("Header validation failed:\n" + msg)
        inputStream.close()
        return

    # Timestamp formatter
    sdf = SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS")
    excelEpoch = Calendar.getInstance()
    excelEpoch.set(1899, 11, 30, 0, 0, 0)  # Excel epoch is Dec 30, 1899

    def format_excel_timestamp(excel_value):
        try:
            millis = long(excel_value * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)
            ts = excelEpoch.getTimeInMillis() + millis
            return sdf.format(ts)
        except:
            return str(excel_value)

    # Parse data rows
    data_rows = []
    for rowIndex in range(sheet.getFirstRowNum() + 1, sheet.getLastRowNum() + 1):
        row = sheet.getRow(rowIndex)
        if row is None:
            continue
        row_dict = {}
        for colIndex in range(headerRow.getFirstCellNum(), headerRow.getLastCellNum()):
            if colIndex >= len(actual_headers):
                continue
            header = actual_headers[colIndex]
            cell = row.getCell(colIndex)
            value = None

            if cell:
                if cell.getCellType() == CellType.STRING:
                    value = cell.getStringCellValue()
                elif cell.getCellType() == CellType.NUMERIC:
                    value = cell.getNumericCellValue()
                elif cell.getCellType() == CellType.BOOLEAN:
                    value = cell.getBooleanCellValue()
                else:
                    value = cell.toString()

            # Format timestamp
            if header.lower() == "timestamp":
                value = format_excel_timestamp(value)

            row_dict[header] = value

        data_rows.append(row_dict)

    # 🔄 Convert to real dataset
    dataset = system.dataset.toDataSet(actual_headers, [
        [row.get(header, None) for header in actual_headers] for row in data_rows
    ])

    # Update view custom properties with real dataset
    self.view.custom.rawDataset = dataset
    self.view.custom.rowCount = dataset.getRowCount()
    self.view.custom.allColumns = actual_headers
    self.view.custom.dropdownOptions = [{"label": "All", "value": "All"}] + [
        {"label": col, "value": col} for col in actual_headers
    ]

    # Update label and table with JSON
    label.props.text = "Valid Table"
    label.props.style.color = "green"
    table.props.data = system.dataset.toPyDataSet(dataset)

    inputStream.close()
